text.tspan: Generic chart title to silence errors
This is an indicator of testing for polio. It shows the share of acute flaccid paralysis (AFP) cases that were tested for
poliovirus and reported to the WHO.
Note: The WHO recommends that the adequate stool collection rate should be at least 80% to ensure that suspected cases are being tested
